HEADWORD: Murrelet
<hw>Murre"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Murre</ets> +
<ets>-let</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of several species
of sea birds of the genera <gen>Synthliboramphus</gen> and
<gen>Brachyramphus</gen>, inhabiting the North Pacific. They are closely
related to the murres.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

